Data were corrected for data acquisition deadtime.
Scattered protons were identified using a
spectrograph, which consists of an array of detectors
First element of array: position-sensitiv helical-wire
Followed by two closely spaced, large plastic
scintillators which served as energy loss detectors
To measure cross sections down to 1 nano-barn/sr,
narrow scintillators, separated by 40 cm and covering
only 20% of the focal plane, were employed.
